The push for a clean up at the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC) and the fight against Jubilee government’s dictatorship will not end, National Super Alliance (NASA) presidential candidate Raila Odinga has vowed.
 Raila said for NASA to participate in the forthcoming presidential elections, a level playing ground must be availed. 
 ALSO READ:

NASA applying ‘lawfare’ tactics in long drawn fight for power

 He said Jubilee is delaying their victory in the polls by increasing obstacles along the way, citing the new electoral rules introduced in Parliament.
 “We are in the 90th minute of play and our teams are level. The referee says we go for the extra time, and then the other team wants to change rules to suit them. Is it practical?” Raila posed.
